modules.description: This module defines standard namespace URIs for HTML, SVG, MathML, XML, and related specifications. It provides string constants for common namespaces, enabling correct qualification of elements and attributes in XML and HTML documents. Use these values when constructing or parsing documents that require namespace-aware processing, such as XHTML, embedded SVG, or XML with xlink references.

This module handles character encoding and decoding for byte streams, primarily used in parsing and serializing HTML and XML. It supports operations like `decode`, which processes a byte stream using a specified encoding and emits Unicode code points, handling invalid sequences by invoking an error reporter. Supported encodings include UTF-8, UTF-16 (both endiannesses), ISO-8859-1, US-ASCII, Windows code pages, and EBCDIC, enabling correct interpretation of encoded text in markup documents.

This module defines an error type for representing parsing and validation issues in HTML and XML documents, including specific cases like decoding failures, mismatched tags, and invalid content. It provides a `to_string` function to convert these errors into human-readable strings, optionally including location information. Concrete use cases include reporting parse errors during streaming XML/HTML processing and debugging malformed documents.
